    • Method Detail

      • needsCoordination

        default boolean needsCoordination()
        Returns:
        True if requests of this type, by default, need to be coordinated or are meant to be executed locally.

      • isNonLocal

        default boolean isNonLocal()
        Returns:
        True if this request needs to contact another active replica in order to complete execution. This flag is different from needsCoordination() above in that the former implies a statically determined replica coordination protocol while this method may involve, say, looking up or writing to a some remote data in a manner specific to executing this request.

      • subRequests

        default RequestType[] subRequests()
        Returns:
        The array of requests that are executed (in order) in order to execute this request. A member of the returned array may itself return a non-null set when subRequests() is invoked upon it. A primitive request, i.e., one with no sub-requests, may return either null or an empty array.

      • isTransaction

        default boolean isTransaction()
        Returns:
        True if subRequests() returns a nonempty array of requests all of which must be executed as a transaction, i.e., with atomicity and isolation. Note that the "C" and "D" in ACID are properties of the replica coordination protocol, so isTransaction() does not imply durability.
